When you create a subtask via REST, it is always added to the end of the list.  However, for performance when creating multiple subtasks, I want to create them asynchronously, which may be out of order.  Therefore, I'd like to be able to create the subtask with a specific sequence id on the created issue link.

This is required for optimal performance in the JIRA Taskmaster plugin being developed for the Plugins 3 Alpha in OnDemand.  We want to be able to fire off the creation of many subtasks all at once and have them ordered in a certain way.  This cannot be done w/o serially creating each subtask after each other, which is quite slow.

